Comment: This command info is generated from fig
Name: zapier
Description: The Zapier CLI is a developer-focused way to create and maintain Zapier integrations. See more at https://github.com/zapier/zapier-platform

Arguments.Name: analytics
Arguments.Description: Show the status of the analytics that are collected. Also used to change what is collected

Arguments.Name: -m
Arguments.Description: Choose how much information to share. Anonymous mode drops the OS type and Zapier user id, but keeps command info. Identifying information is used only for debugging purposes

Arguments.Name: build
Arguments.Description: Build a pushable zip from the current directory

Arguments.Name: --disable-dependency-detection
Arguments.Description: Disable "smart" file inclusion. By default, Zapier only includes files that are required by `index.js`. If you (or your dependencies) require files dynamically (such as with `require(someVar)`), then you may see "Cannot find module" errors. Disabling this may make your `build.zip` too large. If that's the case, try using the `includeInBuild` option in your `.zapierapprc`. See the docs about `includeInBuild` for more info

Arguments.Name: register
Arguments.Description: Register a new integration in your account

Arguments.Name: scaffold
Arguments.Description: Add a starting trigger, create, search, or resource to your integration

Arguments.Name: -d
Arguments.Description: Specify the new file's directory. Use this flag when you want to create a different folder structure such as `src/triggers` instead of the default `triggers`. Defaults to `[triggers|searches|creates]/{noun}`

Arguments.Name: --test-dest
Arguments.Description: Specify the new test file's directory. Use this flag when you want to create a different folder structure such as `src/triggers` instead of the default `triggers`. Defaults to `test/[triggers|searches|creates]/{noun}`

Arguments.Name: -e
Arguments.Description: Supply the path to your integration's root (`index.js`). Only needed if your `index.js` is in a subfolder, like `src`

Arguments.Name: -f
Arguments.Description: Should we overwrite an existing trigger/search/create file?

Arguments.Name: --no-help
Arguments.Description: When scaffolding, should we skip adding helpful intro comments? Useful if this isn't your first rodeo
